              "id": "CVE-2025-14819-curl",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactDirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2025-14819 medium vulnerability for curl package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "When doing TLS related transfers with reused easy or multi handles and altering the  `CURLSSLOPT_NO_PARTIALCHAIN` option, libcurl could accidentally reuse a CA store cached in memory for which the partial chain option was reversed. Contrary to the user's wishes and expectations. This could make libcurl find and accept a trust chain that it otherwise would not."
