              "id": "CVE-2025-30258-gpgv",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2025-30258 medium vulnerability for gpgv package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "In GnuPG before 2.5.5, if a user chooses to import a certificate with certain crafted subkey data that lacks a valid backsig or that has incorrect usage flags, the user loses the ability to verify signatures made from certain other signing keys, aka a \"verification DoS.\""
