            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-22185-libldap-2.5-0",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-22185 low vulnerability for libldap-2.5-0 package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "OpenLDAP Lightning Memory-Mapped Database (LMDB) versions up to and including 0.9.14, prior to commit 8e1fda8, contain a heap buffer underflow in the readline() function of mdb_load. When processing malformed input containing an embedded NUL byte, an unsigned offset calculation can underflow and cause an out-of-bounds read of one byte before the allocated heap buffer. This can cause mdb_load to crash, leading to a limited denial-of-service condition."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://github.com/anchore/grype",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-22185\nSeverity: low\nPackage: libldap-2.5-0\nVersion: 2.5.13+dfsg-5\nFix Version: \nType: deb\nLocation: /var/lib/dpkg/status\nData Namespace: debian:distro:debian:12\nLink: [CVE-2026-22185](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-22185)",
